INSERT INTO `field_body` (`pages_id`, `data`, `data1059`) VALUES('1061', '<p>Current situation</p>\n\n<p>Currently used Orchard CMS installed in 2014. There is no support nor know-how from current service provider.</p>\n\n<p>Proposal</p>\n\n<p>Move Smart homepage to new CMS platform.<br />\nBusiness requirements for Smart homepage CMS</p>\n\n<h2>User view</h2>\n\n<ul><li>As a user I want to check information about Smart products and prices on a Smart homepage.</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to see Smart product pictures on Smart homepage</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to see Smart running campaigns and promo-offers/news</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to read campaign detailed info and detailed conditions</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to see biggest Smart promotions on Smart homepage frontpage (banners)</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to navigate between different sections/pages of Smart homepage via upper menu, left menu, header and footer, also to navigate to related pages (Tele2 pages, Smart selfcare pages, Smart FB page etc)</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to read information in Estonian and Russian language. As a user I want language selection to remain same when moving from/to Smart page to/from other Tele2 pages e.g Smart selfcare, Tele2 homepage, Tele2 eshop or Tele2 selfcare</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to search for specific information inside Smart pages</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to know and accept if my actions on a Smart pages are recorded (cookies)</li>\n	<li>As a user I want to see Smart page on different devices e.g smartphone, notepad, pc</li>\n</ul><h2>Product manager</h2>\n\n<ul><li>As a product manager I want to have Smart homepage with smart.tele2.ee address</li>\n	<li>As a product manager I want to have similar links as smartkaart.ee and tele2.ee/smart to be redirected to smart.tele2.ee address</li>\n	<li>As a product manager I want Smart pages to load within reasonable time (under 3 sec)</li>\n</ul><h2>2. Admin GUI</h2>\n\n<ul><li>As a product owner (further PO) I want to manage Smart homepage content and structure via admin panel / GUI.</li>\n	<li>As a PO I want admin GUI to be accessible in Tele2 internal network with user/password.</li>\n	<li>As a PO I want to have different levels of access to admin GUI</li>\n	<li>o Administrator</li>\n	<li>o Content manager</li>\n	<li>o CSR (not MVP)</li>\n</ul><p>Access levels description:</p>\n\n<ul><li>§ Administrator – can manage GUI users (add new, manage accesses, remove), can manage web structure incl header/footer, can add new templates and page elements, can manage CSS, can add scripts across all Smart pages (GA scripts and alike), have all access that content manager and CSR have, can view logs</li>\n	<li>§ Content manager – can add new pages, manage content of existing pages and remove/archive pages, can upload images, can update/change navigation menu</li>\n	<li>§ CSR – can change content on existing pages (e.g fix links and spelling errors).</li>\n</ul><ul><li>As a PO I want to have GUI content change logs, so it would be possible to track who did what changes in the CMS.</li>\n	<li>As a PO I want to have internal search functionality for Smart content pages. (? What requirements needed here, usually it\'s built-in module)</li>\n	<li>As a PO I want Smart page to be in accordance with data protection law (cookie policy etc)</li>\n	<li>As a PO I want Smart page to be responsive (not MVP, will require redesign).</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to create new pages based on available templates: simple content page and campaign page</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to manage existing pages (content pages, campaign pages, campaign list page, frontpage or other templates).</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to add/change/delete content in a simple way without risk of breaking all Smart homepage nor bigger programming skills needs.</li>\n	<li>As a content manager if needed I should be able to add scripts on concrete page and do other changes in page html.</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to create duplicates of existing pages e.g for different language version or for faster new page creation.</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to set page title, page URL, page text and other page parameters and objects. For campaign pages I want to set additionally campaign pictures, campaign short intro and campaign order/priority. For front page I want to set banners and banner URL\'s. (Front page should be redesigned)</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to set page meta titles, description, canonical URL, tags and other SEO parameters.</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to have versions of content I created with timestamp and index for each version of each content page. As a content manager I should be able to change what version of content page is active e.g I should be able to roll-back to previous version(s).</li>\n	<li>As a content manages I want to select when content is published – there should be possibility to save content without publishing, preview content, publish in real time and publish with future date &amp; time specified.</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to add pictures or other files (videos?) to pages. Pictures are uploaded to CMS media folder before from local machine. It should be possible to create folder structure – product pictures, campaign pictures, banners, thumbnails etc. For front-page videos, banners and campaign pictures, thumbnails should be automatically generated by system.</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to delete pages. Deleted pages should go to recycle bin from where they can be restored if needed. No content page is actually permanently deleted.</li>\n	<li>As a content manager I want to navigate easily to content page or be able to search for page in admin GUI via navigation menu or internal search. In such navigation tree I should see title of a page, page template type, id , version, state, publish timestamp, created and last modified by, language version and other version. Also it should be possible to navigate to that page fast, publish/unpublish, duplicate or delete.</li>\n</ul><p>As a content manager I want to add new pages or blocks to site menu, manage menu tree or remove old pages or blocks from menu tree.</p>\n\n<p>On a Smart page there are upper menu (1st level) and left menu (2nd level) and sub-menus in left menu (3rd level or more). It is possible to change menu with drag-and-drop method. Select what kind of class menu item is (leads to internal page, external page, has text, picture etc). Menu Item parameters are set by its class (e.g external link will have text and destination address, internal link will have text and content page ID).</p>\n\n<ul><li>As an administrator I can add new GUI users and assign access role to them. As an administrator I can update existing users profile or delete users.</li>\n	<li>As an administrator I can manage global Smart pages structure – header, background picture, footer, CSS</li>\n	<li>As an administrator I can create/add new templates for pages (e.g landing pages with different structure or different CSS).</li>\n	<li>As an administrator I can add/remove language versions (e.g add eng version possibility).</li>\n	<li>As an administrator I can add global scripts to all Smart pages (like GTM script)</li>\n	<li>As an administrator I can view logs (what should be in logs? IP, user, timestamp, action, changed content old/new, access details like browser version etc?)</li>\n</ul><p>3. Integrations, external sources and scripts</p>\n\n<p>On page http://smart.tele2.ee/hinnad/koned-valismaal roaming pricelist is taken from internal DB (teletark/intra &gt; https://teletark.tele2.ee/index.php?pi=kkroam). Roaming prices are not changed very often and there is a possibility to push updates to a homepage on demand.</p>\n\n<p>Smart CMS pages should have GTM and Google Optimize scripts (all other will go via GTM).</p>\n\n<p>Smart language selection should be forwarded when navigating to other Tele2 pages – Smart selfcare, Tele2 homepage, selfcare and e-shop.</p>', '');
